Load results

Read in the output file from GEMMA.

results <- read_tsv("gwas/output/f2.assoc.txt")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   chr = col_double(),
##   rs = col_character(),
##   ps = col_double(),
##   n_miss = col_double(),
##   allele1 = col_double(),
##   allele0 = col_double(),
##   af = col_double(),
##   beta = col_double(),
##   se = col_double(),
##   logl_H1 = col_double(),
##   l_remle = col_double(),
##   l_mle = col_double(),
##   p_wald = col_double(),
##   p_lrt = col_double(),
##   p_score = col_double()
## )

Manhattan plot

We use functions from the qqman package to make the typical Manhattan and qq-plots.

manhattan(results, chr = "chr", p = "p_wald", snp = "rs", bp = "ps")

Significant markers:

as.data.frame(filter(results, p_wald < 5e-8))

Quantile-quantile plot

qq(results$p_wald)

Plot of genotypes at a significant marker

We pull out the data underlying the two significant hits and plot them.

geno <- read_tsv("data/txt/geno.txt")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   .default = col_double()
## )
## See spec(...) for full column specifications.
pheno <- read_tsv("data/txt/pheno.txt")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   id = col_double(),
##   trait = col_double(),
##   sex = col_character()
## )
geno_pheno <- inner_join(geno,
                         pheno)
## Joining, by = "id"
qplot(x = factor(SNP_7198),
      y = trait,
      data = geno_pheno,
      geom = "boxplot") +
    facet_wrap(~ sex)
## Warning: Removed 220 rows containing non-finite values (stat_boxplot).

qplot(x = factor(SNP_14704),
      y = trait,
      data = geno_pheno,
      geom = "boxplot") +
    facet_wrap(~ sex)
## Warning: Removed 220 rows containing non-finite values (stat_boxplot).

Example of a somewhat prettier plot (with hypothetical alleles on the x-axis):

ggplot(aes(x = factor(SNP_14704),
           y = trait),
       data = filter(geno_pheno, sex == "F")) +
    geom_boxplot() +
    geom_jitter(colour = "grey") +    
    scale_x_discrete(breaks = 0:2,
                     labels = c("CC", "CA", "AA")) +
    xlab("Genotype") +
    ylab("Trait value") +
    theme_bw() +
    theme(panel.grid = element_blank())
## Warning: Removed 110 rows containing non-finite values (stat_boxplot).
## Warning: Removed 110 rows containing missing values (geom_point).
